        <h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

        <h3 id="when-to-use">When to use</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>A List Item Template will most commonly be used within a
            <Hds::Link::Inline @route="components.list-item">List Item
              (container)</Hds::Link::Inline>. It can also be nested within
            other components as a template.</li>
        </ul>
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-usage.svg"
          alt="List Item demo with List Item Template being used inside of it"
        />

        <h3 id="when-not-to-use">When not to use</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>When your content within is more than 3 lines tall, consider
            creating your own template.</li>
          <li>If you need to make use of styles or nested components that are
            not already available within the template.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="interactivity-and-actions">Interactivity & actions</h2>
        <p>By default the List Item Template is static in nature. Interactivity
          can be applied to elements within, but should adhere to the following
          guidelines.</p>

        <h3 id="tooltips">Tooltips</h3>
        <p>Tooltips can be paired with the template for text, icon, or badge
          elements that need to provide more context on hover. For example, when
          the List Item Template is within a List Item (container).</p>
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-tooltips.svg"
          alt="Demonstration of tooltips on the List Item Template"
        />

        <h3 id="interactivity-specific-elements">Interactivity on a specific
          element</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            If paired with the List Item (container) the state of the container
            should be set to “static”, meaning that clicking on the entire list
            is non-interactive and only individual elements would be.
          </li>
          <li>
            On hover of clickable data, the background color of the object
            hovered should change to
            <Hds::Link::Inline
              @href="https://helios.hashicorp.design/foundations/colors?tab=palette#surface-1"
            >“Surface/interactive-hover”</Hds::Link::Inline>. If the action is
            to copy text then the default copy icon will show.
          </li>
          <li>
            When adding interactivity to an individual element such as a piece
            of text, consider adding a link style (underline or color change) to
            signify that it is interactive if this is the main action of the
            list item.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-interactivity.svg"
          alt="Demonstration of List Item Template interactivity"
        />

        <h2 id="color">Color</h2>
        <h3 id="transparent-background">Transparent background</h3>
        <p>The List Item Template has a transparent background color by default.
          It is set to transparent so it utilizes the background color of
          whatever component it is nested within. This can be changed manually
          as needed.</p>
        <h3 id="title">Title</h3>
        <p>Any text used within the “title” should use HDS text style of
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://helios.hashicorp.design/foundations/colors?tab=palette#foreground-1"
          >“Foreground/Strong”</Hds::Link::Inline>.</p>
        <h3 id="description">Description</h3>
        <p>Any text used within the “description” should use HDS text style of
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://helios.hashicorp.design/foundations/colors?tab=palette#foreground-1"
          >“Foreground/Faint”</Hds::Link::Inline>.</p>
        <h3 id="icons">Icons</h3>
        <p>Any icon used should use the coloring as stated above based on the
          section they are within. Exceptions to this rule are if the icon is
          representing a company or brand logo, or if the icon is representing a
          status.</p>
        <h2 id="size">Size</h2>
        <p>The template horizontal and vertical size preferences can be modified
          depending on the placement of the template. When paired with the list
          Item component use the height and width suggestions listed below.</p>

        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-content.svg"
          alt="List Item Template size guidelines"
        />
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-padding.svg"
          alt="List Item Template padding guidelines"
        />
        <h3 id="height">Height</h3>
        <p>The default height of the template is 56px for desktop (large) screen
          sizes, this is the recommended max limit for the height of this
          component.</p>
        <h3 id="width">Width</h3>
        <p>The width of the list item should “fill” the entire section that it
          is placed within.
        </p>
        <Hds::Alert @type="inline" @color="highlight" as |A|>
          <A.Title>
            It is important to keep list items that are displayed on the same
            page a consistent size (height and width).</A.Title>
        </Hds::Alert>
        <h3 id="responsive">Responsive layout</h3>
        <p>The List Item Template has two states, “Large” and “”Small”.</p>
        <h3 id="large">Large (default)</h3>
        <p>The large variant will fill the entire width of whichever it is
          contained within by default.
        </p>
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-responsive-large.svg"
          alt="List Item Template should fill the entired width of it's container on larger screens."
        />
        <h3 id="small">Small (mobile)</h3>
        <p>The small variant will have a max width of 318px, when placed in a
          container you will need to set the container width to “hug”.</p>
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-responsive-small.svg"
          alt="List Item Template small details"
        />
