        <h2 id="component-anatomy">Component anatomy</h2>
        <p>The List Item Template is made up from nested components. Below is
          the anatomy for the individual components. For more details on their
          respective APIs, view the component API section under the code tab.</p>

        <h3 id="section">Label</h3>
        <p>The List Item Template Section is the primary part of the template.
          It consists of a title, and an optional icon for the title, as well as
          an area to place metadata like badges, labels, etc. There are two
          available Sections in the List Item Template. The first is required
          and is available via the
          <CodeInline @code="Section" />
          contextual component. The second Section is optional and can be used
          via the
          <CodeInline @code="SecondSection" />
          contextual component.</p>
        <img
          src="/images/list-item-template-section.svg"
          alt="List Item Template Section Anatomy"
        />

        <h3 id="connection-method">Connection Method</h3>
        <p>
          The List Item Template provides two different component options for
          the Connection Method, an
          <CodeInline @code="Icon" />
          and a
          <CodeInline @code="Badge" />. Both using the
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://helios.hashicorp.design/icons/usage-guidelines"
          >Icon</Hds::Link::Inline>
          and
          <Hds::Link::Inline
            @href="https://helios.hashicorp.design/components/badge"
          >Badge</Hds::Link::Inline>
          components from HDS respectively. The connection Method option is only
          available if the second section is visible and will be displayed
          between each section.
        </p>
